''This is a [[Chinese name]]; the family name is A.'' {{Infobox Chinese-language singer and actor <!------See WikiProject Chinese-language entertainment-------> |name = Liya A |gender = female |image = Ae6a8b09gw1f4pax5sgglj223u35skjl.jpg |caption = | background = actor_or_actress |chinesename = |tradchinesename = 阿麗亞 |simpchinesename = 阿丽亚 |pinyinchinesename = |jyutpingchinesename = |birth_name = |ethnicity = [[Mongols|Mongolian]] |ancestry = |origin = |birth_date = {{birth date and age|mf=yes|1992|05|10}} |birth_place = [[Inner Mongolia]], [[People's Republic of China|China]] |death_date = |death_place = |restingplace = |restingplacecoordinates = |othername = |occupation = [[Actress]] |label= |alma_mater =[[Shanghai Theatre Academy]] |instrument = |voicetype = |yearsactive = 2013–present |currentmembers = |pastmembers = |associatedact = |spouse = |sibling = |children = |parents = |influences = |influenced = |website = |hongkongfilmwards = |goldenbauhiniaawards = |hkfcsawards = |goldenhorseawards = |goldenroosterawards = |hundredflowersawards = |mtvasiaawards = |goldenmelodyawards = |ntsawards = |tvbanniversaryawards = |awards = }} '''Aliya''' (Chinese 阿丽亚, born 10 May 1992) also romanised as '''Liya A''', is a Chinese Mongolian actress. She was educated at [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]]. Her first play was the television series ''The Spring of Gallows'' in 2013. She also played leading roles in the web dramas ''In Tale of Flower'' and ''Gamer's Generation'', and is also known for her supporting role in the fantasy television series ''[[Novoland: The Castle in the Sky]]''.
==Early life and education== Aliya was born in [[Inner Mongolia]], China. In 2011, she enrolled as an undergraduate in [[Shanghai Theatre Academy]], where she majored in acting.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://news.hexun.com/2016-08-08/185395837.html|title=生活中我还是 很有女人味的|date=August 8, 2016|website=Hexun|language=zh}}</ref> She worked part-time as a model.
