{{Infobox cricketer | name = | image = | country = Pakistan | fullname = Pervez Iqbal | nickname = | birth_date = {{Birth date|1975|12|26|df=yes}} | birth_place = [[Rawalpindi]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]], [[Pakistan]] | death_date = {{Death date and age|2002|3|11|1975|12|26|df=yes}} | death_place = Rawalpindi, Punjab, Pakistan | heightft = | heightinch = | batting = Left-handed | bowling = Right-arm [[Seam bowling|medium]] | role = | family = | club1 = [[Derbyshire Cricket Board]] | year1 = 2000 | clubnumber1 = | club2 = [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi A]] | year2 = 1995/96 | clubnumber2 = | club3 = [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi B]] | year3 = 1994/95-1995/96 | clubnumber3 = | club4 = [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi]] | year4 = 1993/94-2000/01 | clubnumber4 = | deliveries = balls | columns = 2 | column1 = [[First-class cricket|FC]] | matches1 = 20 | runs1 = 602 | bat avg1 = 20.06 | 100s/50s1 = &ndash;/4 | top score1 = 76 | deliveries1 = 2,412 | wickets1 = 46 | bowl avg1 = 25.71 | fivefor1 = 1 | tenfor1 = &ndash; | best bowling1 = 1/59 | catches/stumpings1 = 2/&ndash; | column2 = [[List-A cricket|LA]] | matches2 = 20 | runs2 = 212 | bat avg2 = 15.14 | 100s/50s2 = &ndash;/1 | top score2 = 56 | deliveries2 = 866 | wickets2 = 25 | bowl avg2 = 22.32 | fivefor2 = 1 | tenfor2 = &ndash; | best bowling2 = 5/22 | catches/stumpings2 = 4/&ndash; | date = 16 October | year = 2010 | source = http://www.cricinfo.com/ci/content/player/42326.html Cricinfo }}
'''Pervez Iqbal''' (26 December 1975 &ndash; 11 March 2002) was a [[Pakistani people|Pakistani]] [[cricket]]er. Iqbal was a left-handed [[Batsman (cricket)|batsman]] who bowled with his right-arm [[Seam bowling|medium pace]]. He was born at [[Rawalpindi]], [[Punjab (Pakistan)|Punjab]].
Iqbal made his [[first-class cricket|first-class]] debut for [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi]] against [[Faisalabad cricket team|Faisalabad]] in 1993/94 season. Iqbal represented the main Rawlpindi team in first-class cricket from the 1993/94 to 2000/01, as well as [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi B]] from 1994/95-1995/96. His final first-class match came for the main Rawalpindi team against [[Lahore cricket team|Lahore Blues]] in 2001.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/10/10967/First-Class_Matches.html First-Class Matches played by Pervez Iqbal]</ref> In total, from 1993/94 to 2000/01 he played 20 first-class matches. In these matches he scored a total of 602 runs at a [[batting average]] of 20.06, with 4 [[half century|half centuries]] and a high score of 76. With the ball he took 46 wickets at a [[bowling average]] of 25.71, with a single [[five wicket haul]] which resulted in his best figures of 5/59.
Iqbal also mde his debut in [[List A cricket]] for Rawalpindi in the 1993/94 season against Faisalabad. Iqbal represented the main Rawalpindi team in List A cricket 11 times from the 1993/94 to 1999/2000 season. In addition, he also represented [[Rawalpindi cricket team|Rawalpindi A]] in 8 matches during the 1995/96 season. His final List-A match for a Rawalpindi team came against [[Islamabad Leopards|Islamabad]] in March 2000.<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Players/10/10967/List_A_Matches.html List A Matches played by Pervez Iqbal]</ref> During the [[2000 English cricket season]], Iqbal played a single List A match for the [[Derbyshire Cricket Board]] in the [[2000 NatWest Trophy]] against the [[Gloucestershire Cricket Board]].<ref>[https://cricketarchive.com/Archive/Scorecards/69/69742.html Derbyshire Cricket Board v Gloucestershire Cricket Board, 2000 NatWest Trophy]</ref> In his total of 20 List A matches, he scored 212 runs at an average of 15.14, with a single half century high score of 56. With the ball he took 25 wickets at an average of 22.32, with a single five wicket haul which gave him best figures of 5/22.
Iqbal died in Rawalpindi, Punjab on 11 March 2002 from a rare pollen [[allergy]].<ref>[http://www.dawn.com/2002/03/19/spt14.htm First-class cricketer Pervez dies]</ref>
