{{Infobox college coach | name = William H. Burke | image = | alt = | caption = | sport = [[American football|Football]] | birth_date = | birth_place = | death_date = | death_place = | alma_mater = | coach_years1 = 1899 | coach_team1 = [[William & Mary Tribe football|William & Mary]] | coach_years2 = 1905–1906 | coach_team2 = [[St. Bonaventure Brown Indians football|St. Bonaventure]] | overall_record = 5–3 | bowl_record = | tournament_record = | championships = | awards = | coaching_records = }} '''William H. Burke''' was the head coach of [[The College of William & Mary]]'s [[William & Mary Tribe football|football team]] in 1899. He coached only one season and compiled a 2–3 record.
After leaving William & Mary, Burke coached for two seasons at [[St. Bonaventure University]] in [[Allegany (town), New York|Allegany]], [[New York (state)|New York]]. He went 1–0 in 1905 and 2–0 in 1906.
